Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Mummy breast cover with from top to bottom: a winged solar disc framed by the two falcon heads of a wesekh-collar; a pectoral with a cavetto cornice adorned with three crouched mummiform deities facing right: Isis (?), Osiris and Nephthys (?) framed by the large and very detailed wesekh-collar; a winged scarab.
